      <bioghist id="aspace_f4afd59d7e02a6940f83c3ce17b54a19">
         <head>Joseph Hillyer Brewer (1898-1991)</head>
         <p>Joseph Hillyer Brewer, American publisher, librarian, and president of Olivet College. He was born in 1898 and died in New York City in 1991.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_d67ec55818254163695b7212574bf122">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The collection contains correspondence, writings, and photographs. Correspondence includes autograph manuscript and typescripts letters from Harold Acton, Iris Barry, Charles Fisk, Katherine Anne Porter, John Strachey and others. There is a small amount of outgoing letters among the correspondence. Writings include autograph and typescript drafts and printed versions of writings by Brewer, including "20th Century Typography in the Netherlands." Photographs include ones by Milton Horn and ones of Katherine Anne Porter by George Platt Lynes.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_eb9fa3a200f921548a7e1533e3454585">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Organized into two series: I. Correspondence, 1922-1979. II. Other Papers, 1930-1976.</p>  
      </arrangement>
